text: Morten Solem (born 5 August 1980) is a Norwegian former ski jumper who competed from 1999 to 2007. His best results at World Cup level were four top 10 finishes, with a seventh place in Liberec on 11 January 2004 as his best individual result. He also finished second overall in the 2002–03 and 2005–06 Continental Cup seasons. ==External links== * Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:Norwegian male ski jumpers
